# Editing this capsule

The server reads .gmi files directly off disk -- no rebuild required
after editing. Three ways to change what this capsule serves:

## 1. Built-in WYSIWYG editor (recommended)

Sign in to your OpenHost compute space, then open:

=> /edit Open the editor

You'll get a sidebar with all .gmi files and a contenteditable view
that maps gemtext line shapes to editor blocks (heading, quote, list
item, link, preformatted). Hit Save and agate serves the new content
on the next request.

The editor lives at the HTTP side of this app (not the Gemini side),
behind the OpenHost session, so only the compute-space owner can use
it.

## 2. File-browser app

If you have the file-browser app installed in this compute space,
open it and navigate to the "gemini" app's data directory. You'll
find a "content/" folder with the .gmi files you see here. Edit,
save, refresh your Gemini client.

## 3. oh app exec (power user)

You can edit files directly from the shell using the OpenHost CLI:

```
oh app exec gemini -- sh -c 'cat > /data/app_data/gemini/content/index.gmi'
```

(Paste your new content, Ctrl-D.)

## gemtext reference

=> gemini://geminiprotocol.net/docs/gemtext-specification.gmi The official gemtext spec

=> / Back to the index
